27 June 2008Government will hold cluster media briefings on the implementation of the Government Programme of Action for 2008, in Pretoria from 30 June to 7 July 2008.This will be the second cycle of media briefings for the year since the announcement of the programme through the State of the Nation Address.The briefings will take place at the Union Buildings, Rooms 153 and 159. There will be a video link-up with Cape Town's Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Cape Town.Briefings schedule:Monday, 30 June 200810:30 - 14:00: Justice, Crime Prevention and Security cluster briefing, and release of crime statistics, chaired by Minister of Safety and Security, Charles Nqakula Venue: Room 159, Union Buildings, PretoriaTuesday, 1 July 200810:00 11:30: Economic Cluster briefing chaired by Minister of Trade and Industry, Mandisi Mpahlwa Venue: Room 153, Union Buildings, Pretoria12:30-14:00: Governance and Administration Cluster briefing chaired by Minister of Public Service and Administration, Geraldine Fraser-Moleketi Venue: Room 153, Union Buildings, PretoriaNB:The International Relations, Peace and Security Cluster and the Social Cluster briefings are still to be confirmed.Enquiries Harold Maloka (Pretoria) Cell: 082 847 9799Colin Cruywagen (Cape Town) Cell: 082 377 9916Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)